## How to run (real execution, no mocks)

```bash
cd drizzle/degrees/01-typed-sql-and-migrations/03-pocs/L-capstone-typed-repository-layer-ci/source
npm install
node --test repository.test.mjs > ../green-output.txt 2>&1; echo "EXIT=$?" >> ../green-output.txt
cat ../green-output.txt
```

Because the redirect form is used (`>` + `2>&1` then `echo $?`), the exit code reflects `node --test`'s own status — not a pipe's status, per the documented gotcha.

## Notes tying implementation to documented behavioral facts

- `createUser` uses the **`lastInsertRowid`**-from-`.run()` pattern (an equivalent alternative to a raw `select last_insert_rowid()` query, and to `.returning().all()/.get()` — all three are confirmed working on `drizzle-orm@0.45.2` + `better-sqlite3`).
- The autoincrement PK correctly emits `null` in generated INSERT SQL (`values (null, ?, ?)`) — SQLite resolves it to the next rowid; verified via the `toSQL()` test.
- `getUser` returns `undefined` (not `null`) on no match — asserted with `!== undefined` / `=== undefined`, not falsy checks.
- `{ logger: false }` is set on the `drizzle()` instance in `db.mjs` to keep `node --test` output limited to the explicit `console.log` lines shown in the expected GREEN transcript.
- The RED bug (`eq(users.name, String(id))`) is preserved as an inline comment in `repository.mjs` for CI-gate documentation purposes but the **shipped code is the fix** (`eq(users.id, id)`) — this is the state that produces `tests 7 / pass 7 / fail 0 / EXIT=0`.

## Honest caveat

`better-sqlite3@12.11.1` is a native addon — first `npm install` on a machine without a matching prebuilt binary will trigger `node-gyp` compilation (needs a C++ toolchain + Python present). If `npm install` fails with a `node-gyp` error, that's an environment/toolchain gap, not a code defect in this repository layer.

