## `fga/model.fga` (reference DSL)

```
model
  schema 1.1

type user

type group
  relations
    define member: [user]

type document
  relations
    define owner: [user]
    define editor: [user, group#member]
    define viewer: [user, group#member] or editor or owner
    define can_share: owner
```

Key design point per the spec's regression requirement: `can_share` is defined as **`owner`** directly (a bare `computedUserset`), *not* a union including `viewer`. Bob is a `viewer` of `document:roadmap` via `group:eng#member`, but that grants him nothing on `can_share`.

## `fga/model.json` (sent to `writeAuthorizationModel`)

```json
{
  "schema_version": "1.1",
  "type_definitions": [
    { "type": "user" },
    {
      "type": "group",
      "relations": { "member": { "this": {} } },
      "metadata": {
        "relations": {
          "member": { "directly_related_user_types": [{ "type": "user" }] }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "document",
      "relations": {
        "owner": { "this": {} },
        "editor": { "this": {} },
        "viewer": {
          "union": {
            "child": [
              { "this": {} },
              { "computedUserset": { "relation": "editor" } },
              { "computedUserset": { "relation": "owner" } }
            ]
          }
        },
        "can_share": { "computedUserset": { "relation": "owner" } }
      },
      "metadata": {
        "relations": {
          "owner": { "directly_related_user_types": [{ "type": "user" }] },
          "editor": {
            "directly_related_user_types": [
              { "type": "user" },
              { "type": "group", "relation": "member" }
            ]
          },
          "viewer": {
            "directly_related_user_types": [
              { "type": "user" },
              { "type": "group", "relation": "member" }
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

`can_share` gets **no** `metadata.relations` entry — it has no `this`/directly-assignable clause, only a `computedUserset`, so OpenFGA's schema validator doesn't require (or accept) direct-type metadata for it.

