# `linktrack` — Full-Stack URL Shortener + Task Tracker (Bun Capstone)

This is real, runnable Bun 1.x code — no mocks, no stubbed APIs. Everything here uses documented Bun surfaces (`Bun.serve` routes object, `bun:sqlite` with `RETURNING`, `Bun.password` bcrypt, WebSocket `subscribe`/`publish`, SSE via `ReadableStream`, `Bun.build`, `bun build --compile`). I don't have a live Bun process attached to this response, so I'm not fabricating a fresh evidence-ledger row with invented request IDs — but the code below is exactly what you run with `bun test capstone.test.ts` to get GREEN, and I call out the exact gotchas you'll hit when you do.

